4887// JavaScript invokes.
4888
4889void MacroAssembler::LoadStackLimit(Register destination, StackLimitKind kind) {
4890 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4891 DCHECK(root_array_available());
4892 intptr_t offset = kind == StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit
4893 ? IsolateData::real_jslimit_offset()
4894 : IsolateData::jslimit_offset();
4895
4896 Ld(destination, MemOperand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset)));
4897}
4898
4899void MacroAssembler::StackOverflowCheck(Register num_args, Register scratch1,
4900 Register scratch2,
4901 Label* stack_overflow) {
4902 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4903 // Check the stack for overflow. We are not trying to catch
4904 // interruptions (e.g. debug break and preemption) here, so the "real stack
4905 // limit" is checked.
4906
4907 LoadStackLimit(scratch1, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
4908 // Make scratch1 the space we have left. The stack might already be overflowed
4909 // here which will cause scratch1 to become negative.
4910 dsubu(scratch1, sp, scratch1);
4911 // Check if the arguments will overflow the stack.
4912 dsll(scratch2, num_args, kPointerSizeLog2);
4913 // Signed comparison.
4914 Branch(stack_overflow, le, scratch1, Operand(scratch2));
4915}
4916
4917#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
4918void MacroAssembler::LoadCodeEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(
4919 Register destination, MemOperand field_operand) {
4920 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4921 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4922 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4923 DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, scratch));
4924 DCHECK_EQ(JSDispatchEntry::kEntrypointOffset, 0);
4925
4926 li(scratch, ExternalReference::js_dispatch_table_address());
4927 Lwu(destination, field_operand);
4928 dsrl(destination, destination, kJSDispatchHandleShift);
4929 dsll(destination, destination, kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2);
4930 Ld(destination, MemOperand(scratch, destination));
4931}
4932#endif
4933
4934void MacroAssembler::TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimizationAndJump(
4935 Register code_data_container, Register scratch, Condition cond,
4936 Label* target) {
4937 Lwu(scratch, FieldMemOperand(code_data_container, Code::kFlagsOffset));
4938 And(scratch, scratch, Operand(1 << Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit));
4939 Branch(target, cond, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
4940}
4941
4942Operand MacroAssembler::ClearedValue() const {
4943 return Operand(static_cast<int32_t>(i::ClearedValue(isolate()).ptr()));
4944}
4945
4946void MacroAssembler::InvokePrologue(Register expected_parameter_count,
4947 Register actual_parameter_count,
4948 Label* done, InvokeType type) {
4949 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4950 Label regular_invoke;
4951
4952 // a0: actual arguments count
4953 // a1: function (passed through to callee)
4954 // a2: expected arguments count
4955
4956 DCHECK_EQ(actual_parameter_count, a0);
4957 DCHECK_EQ(expected_parameter_count, a2);
4958
4959 // If overapplication or if the actual argument count is equal to the
4960 // formal parameter count, no need to push extra undefined values.
4961 Dsubu(expected_parameter_count, expected_parameter_count,
4962 actual_parameter_count);
4963 Branch(&regular_invoke, le, expected_parameter_count, Operand(zero_reg));
4964
4965 Label stack_overflow;
4966 StackOverflowCheck(expected_parameter_count, t0, t1, &stack_overflow);
4967 // Underapplication. Move the arguments already in the stack, including the
4968 // receiver and the return address.
4969 {
4970 Label copy;
4971 Register src = a6, dest = a7;
4972 mov(src, sp);
4973 dsll(t0, expected_parameter_count, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
4974 Dsubu(sp, sp, Operand(t0));
4975 // Update stack pointer.
4976 mov(dest, sp);
4977 mov(t0, actual_parameter_count);
4978 bind(&copy);
4979 Ld(t1, MemOperand(src, 0));
4980 Sd(t1, MemOperand(dest, 0));
4981 Dsubu(t0, t0, Operand(1));
4982 Daddu(src, src, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
4983 Daddu(dest, dest, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
4984 Branch(&copy, gt, t0, Operand(zero_reg));
4985 }
4986
4987 // Fill remaining expected arguments with undefined values.
4988 LoadRoot(t0, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
4989 {
4990 Label loop;
4991 bind(&loop);
4992 Sd(t0, MemOperand(a7, 0));
4993 Dsubu(expected_parameter_count, expected_parameter_count, Operand(1));
4994 Daddu(a7, a7, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
4995 Branch(&loop, gt, expected_parameter_count, Operand(zero_reg));
4996 }
4997 b(&regular_invoke);
4998 nop();
4999
5000 bind(&stack_overflow);
5001 {
5002 FrameScope frame(
5003 this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
5004 CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStackOverflow);
5005 break_(0xCC);
5006 }
5007
5008 bind(&regular_invoke);
5009}
5010
5011void MacroAssembler::CheckDebugHook(Register fun, Register new_target,
5012 Register expected_parameter_count,
5013 Register actual_parameter_count) {
5014 Label skip_hook;
5015
5016 li(t0, ExternalReference::debug_hook_on_function_call_address(isolate()));
5017 Lb(t0, MemOperand(t0));
5018 Branch(&skip_hook, eq, t0, Operand(zero_reg));
5019
5020 {
5021 // Load receiver to pass it later to DebugOnFunctionCall hook.
5022 LoadReceiver(t0);
5023
5024 FrameScope frame(
5025 this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
5026 SmiTag(expected_parameter_count);
5027 Push(expected_parameter_count);
5028
5029 SmiTag(actual_parameter_count);
5030 Push(actual_parameter_count);
5031
5032 if (new_target.is_valid()) {
5033 Push(new_target);
5034 }
5035 Push(fun);
5036 Push(fun);
5037 Push(t0);
5038 CallRuntime(Runtime::kDebugOnFunctionCall);
5039 Pop(fun);
5040 if (new_target.is_valid()) {
5041 Pop(new_target);
5042 }
5043
5044 Pop(actual_parameter_count);
5045 SmiUntag(actual_parameter_count);
5046
5047 Pop(expected_parameter_count);
5048 SmiUntag(expected_parameter_count);
5049 }
5050 bind(&skip_hook);
5051}
5052
5053void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionCode(Register function, Register new_target,
5054 Register expected_parameter_count,
5055 Register actual_parameter_count,
5056 InvokeType type) {
5057 // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5058 DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
5059 DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5060 DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_target.is_valid(), new_target == a3);
5061
5062 // On function call, call into the debugger if necessary.
5063 CheckDebugHook(function, new_target, expected_parameter_count,
5064 actual_parameter_count);
5065
5066 // Clear the new.target register if not given.
5067 if (!new_target.is_valid()) {
5068 LoadRoot(a3, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5069 }
5070
5071 Label done;
5072 InvokePrologue(expected_parameter_count, actual_parameter_count, &done, type);
5073 // We call indirectly through the code field in the function to
5074 // allow recompilation to take effect without changing any of the
5075 // call sites.
5076 switch (type) {
5077 case InvokeType::kCall:
5078 CallJSFunction(function);
5079 break;
5080 case InvokeType::kJump:
5081 JumpJSFunction(function);
5082 break;
5083 }
5084
5085 // Continue here if InvokePrologue does handle the invocation due to
5086 // mismatched parameter counts.
5087 bind(&done);
5088}
5089
5090void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionWithNewTarget(
5091 Register function, Register new_target, Register actual_parameter_count,
5092 InvokeType type) {
5093 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5094 // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5095 DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
5096
5097 // Contract with called JS functions requires that function is passed in a1.
5098 DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5099 Register expected_parameter_count = a2;
5100 Register temp_reg = t0;
5101 Ld(temp_reg, FieldMemOperand(a1, JSFunction::kSharedFunctionInfoOffset));
5102 Ld(cp, FieldMemOperand(a1, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
5103 // The argument count is stored as uint16_t
5104 Lhu(expected_parameter_count,
5105 FieldMemOperand(temp_reg,
5106 SharedFunctionInfo::kFormalParameterCountOffset));
5107
5108 InvokeFunctionCode(a1, new_target, expected_parameter_count,
5109 actual_parameter_count, type);
5110}
5111
5112void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunction(Register function,
5113 Register expected_parameter_count,
5114 Register actual_parameter_count,
5115 InvokeType type) {
5116 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5117 // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5118 DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
5119
5120 // Contract with called JS functions requires that function is passed in a1.
5121 DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5122
5123 // Get the function and setup the context.
5124 Ld(cp, FieldMemOperand(a1, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
5125
5126 InvokeFunctionCode(a1, no_reg, expected_parameter_count,
5127 actual_parameter_count, type);
5128}
5129
5130// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
5131// Support functions.
5132
5133void MacroAssembler::GetObjectType(Register object, Register map,
5134 Register type_reg) {
5135 LoadMap(map, object);
5136 Lhu(type_reg, FieldMemOperand(map, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
5137}
5138
5139void MacroAssembler::GetInstanceTypeRange(Register map, Register type_reg,
5140 InstanceType lower_limit,
5141 Register range) {
5142 Lhu(type_reg, FieldMemOperand(map, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
5143 Dsubu(range, type_reg, Operand(lower_limit));
5144}
5145
5146// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5147// Runtime calls.
5148
5149void MacroAssembler::DaddOverflow(Register dst, Register left,
5150 const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
5151 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5152 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5153 Register right_reg = no_reg;
5154 Register scratch = t8;
5155 if (!right.is_reg()) {
5156 li(at, Operand(right));
5157 right_reg = at;
5158 } else {
5159 right_reg = right.rm();
5160 }
5161
5162 DCHECK(left != scratch && right_reg != scratch && dst != scratch &&
5163 overflow != scratch);
5164 DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
5165
5166 if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
5167 daddu(scratch, left, right_reg);
5168 xor_(overflow, scratch, left);
5169 xor_(at, scratch, right_reg);
5170 and_(overflow, overflow, at);
5171 mov(dst, scratch);
5172 } else {
5173 daddu(dst, left, right_reg);
5174 xor_(overflow, dst, left);
5175 xor_(at, dst, right_reg);
5176 and_(overflow, overflow, at);
5177 }
5178}
5179
5180void MacroAssembler::DsubOverflow(Register dst, Register left,
5181 const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
5182 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5183 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5184 Register right_reg = no_reg;
5185 Register scratch = t8;
5186 if (!right.is_reg()) {
5187 li(at, Operand(right));
5188 right_reg = at;
5189 } else {
5190 right_reg = right.rm();
5191 }
5192
5193 DCHECK(left != scratch && right_reg != scratch && dst != scratch &&
5194 overflow != scratch);
5195 DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
5196
5197 if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
5198 dsubu(scratch, left, right_reg);
5199 xor_(overflow, left, scratch);
5200 xor_(at, left, right_reg);
5201 and_(overflow, overflow, at);
5202 mov(dst, scratch);
5203 } else {
5204 dsubu(dst, left, right_reg);
5205 xor_(overflow, left, dst);
5206 xor_(at, left, right_reg);
5207 and_(overflow, overflow, at);
5208 }
5209}
5210
5211void MacroAssembler::MulOverflow(Register dst, Register left,
5212 const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
5213 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5214 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5215 Register right_reg = no_reg;
5216 Register scratch = t8;
5217 if (!right.is_reg()) {
5218 li(at, Operand(right));
5219 right_reg = at;
5220 } else {
5221 right_reg = right.rm();
5222 }
5223
5224 DCHECK(left != scratch && right_reg != scratch && dst != scratch &&
5225 overflow != scratch);
5226 DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
5227
5228 if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
5229 Mul(scratch, left, right_reg);
5230 Mulh(overflow, left, right_reg);
5231 mov(dst, scratch);
5232 } else {
5233 Mul(dst, left, right_reg);
5234 Mulh(overflow, left, right_reg);
5235 }
5236
5237 dsra32(scratch, dst, 0);
5238 xor_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
5239}
5240
5241void MacroAssembler::DMulOverflow(Register dst, Register left,
5242 const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
5243 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5244 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5245 Register right_reg = no_reg;
5246 Register scratch = t8;
5247 if (!right.is_reg()) {
5248 li(at, Operand(right));
5249 right_reg = at;
5250 } else {
5251 right_reg = right.rm();
5252 }
5253
5254 DCHECK(left != scratch && right_reg != scratch && dst != scratch &&
5255 overflow != scratch);
5256 DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
5257
5258 if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
5259 Dmul(scratch, left, right_reg);
5260 Dmulh(overflow, left, right_reg);
5261 mov(dst, scratch);
5262 } else {
5263 Dmul(dst, left, right_reg);
5264 Dmulh(overflow, left, right_reg);
5265 }
5266
5267 dsra32(scratch, dst, 31);
5268 xor_(overflow, overflow, scratch);
5269}
5270
5271void MacroAssembler::CallRuntime(const Runtime::Function* f,
5272 int num_arguments) {
5273 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5274 // All parameters are on the stack. v0 has the return value after call.
5275
5276 // If the expected number of arguments of the runtime function is
5277 // constant, we check that the actual number of arguments match the
5278 // expectation.
5279 CHECK(f->nargs < 0 || f->nargs == num_arguments);
5280
5281 // TODO(1236192): Most runtime routines don't need the number of
5282 // arguments passed in because it is constant. At some point we
5283 // should remove this need and make the runtime routine entry code
5284 // smarter.
5285 PrepareCEntryArgs(num_arguments);
5286 PrepareCEntryFunction(ExternalReference::Create(f));
5287 bool switch_to_central_stack = options().is_wasm;
5288 CallBuiltin(Builtins::RuntimeCEntry(f->result_size, switch_to_central_stack));
5289}
5290
5291void MacroAssembler::TailCallRuntime(Runtime::FunctionId fid) {
5292 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5293 const Runtime::Function* function = Runtime::FunctionForId(fid);
5294 DCHECK_EQ(1, function->result_size);
5295 if (function->nargs >= 0) {
5296 PrepareCEntryArgs(function->nargs);
5297 }
5298 JumpToExternalReference(ExternalReference::Create(fid));
5299}
5300
5301void MacroAssembler::JumpToExternalReference(const ExternalReference& builtin,
5302 bool builtin_exit_frame) {
5303 PrepareCEntryFunction(builtin);
5304 TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::CEntry(1, ArgvMode::kStack, builtin_exit_frame));
5305}
5306
5307void MacroAssembler::LoadWeakValue(Register out, Register in,
5308 Label* target_if_cleared) {
5309 Branch(target_if_cleared, eq, in, Operand(kClearedWeakHeapObjectLower32));
5310
5311 And(out, in, Operand(~kWeakHeapObjectMask));
5312}
5313
5314void MacroAssembler::EmitIncrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value,
5315 Register scratch1,
5316 Register scratch2) {
5317 DCHECK_GT(value, 0);
5318 if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
5319 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5320 // This operation has to be exactly 32-bit wide in case the external
5321 // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t dummy_stats_counter_
5322 // field.
5323 li(scratch2, ExternalReference::Create(counter));
5324 Lw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
5325 Addu(scratch1, scratch1, Operand(value));
5326 Sw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
5327 }
5328}
5329
5330void MacroAssembler::EmitDecrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value,
5331 Register scratch1,
5332 Register scratch2) {
5333 DCHECK_GT(value, 0);
5334 if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
5335 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5336 // This operation has to be exactly 32-bit wide in case the external
5337 // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t dummy_stats_counter_
5338 // field.
5339 li(scratch2, ExternalReference::Create(counter));
5340 Lw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
5341 Subu(scratch1, scratch1, Operand(value));
5342 Sw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
5343 }
5344}
5345
5346// -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
5347// Debugging.
5348
5349void MacroAssembler::Trap() { stop(); }
5350void MacroAssembler::DebugBreak() { stop(); }
5351
5352void MacroAssembler::Check(Condition cc, AbortReason reason, Register rs,
5353 Operand rt) {
5354 Label L;
5355 Branch(&L, cc, rs, rt);
5356 Abort(reason);
5357 // Will not return here.
5358 bind(&L);
5359}
5360
5361void MacroAssembler::Abort(AbortReason reason) {
5362 Label abort_start;
5363 bind(&abort_start);
5364 if (v8_flags.code_comments) {
5365 const char* msg = GetAbortReason(reason);
5366 RecordComment("Abort message: ");
5367 RecordComment(msg);
5368 }
5369
5370 // Avoid emitting call to builtin if requested.
5371 if (trap_on_abort()) {
5372 stop();
5373 return;
5374 }
5375
5376 if (should_abort_hard()) {
5377 // We don't care if we constructed a frame. Just pretend we did.
5378 FrameScope assume_frame(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
5379 PrepareCallCFunction(1, a0);
5380 li(a0, Operand(static_cast<int>(reason)));
5381 li(a1, ExternalReference::abort_with_reason());
5382 // Use Call directly to avoid any unneeded overhead. The function won't
5383 // return anyway.
5384 Call(a1);
5385 return;
5386 }
5387
5388 Move(a0, Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(reason)));
5389
5390 {
5391 // We don't actually want to generate a pile of code for this, so just
5392 // claim there is a stack frame, without generating one.
5393 FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
5394 if (root_array_available()) {
5395 // Generate an indirect call via builtins entry table here in order to
5396 // ensure that the interpreter_entry_return_pc_offset is the same for
5397 // InterpreterEntryTrampoline and InterpreterEntryTrampolineForProfiling
5398 // when v8_flags.debug_code is enabled.
5399 LoadEntryFromBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort, t9);
5400 Call(t9);
5401 } else {
5402 CallBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort);
5403 }
5404 }
5405 // Will not return here.
5406 if (is_trampoline_pool_blocked()) {
5407 // If the calling code cares about the exact number of
5408 // instructions generated, we insert padding here to keep the size
5409 // of the Abort macro constant.
5410 // Currently in debug mode with debug_code enabled the number of
5411 // generated instructions is 10, so we use this as a maximum value.
5412 static const int kExpectedAbortInstructions = 10;
5413 int abort_instructions = InstructionsGeneratedSince(&abort_start);
5414 DCHECK_LE(abort_instructions, kExpectedAbortInstructions);
5415 while (abort_instructions++ < kExpectedAbortInstructions) {
5416 nop();
5417 }
5418 }
5419}
5420
5421void MacroAssembler::LoadMap(Register destination, Register object) {
5422 Ld(destination, FieldMemOperand(object, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
5423}
5424
5425void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVector(Register dst, Register closure,
5426 Register scratch, Label* fbv_undef) {
5427 Label done;
5428 // Load the feedback vector from the closure.
5429 Ld(dst, FieldMemOperand(closure, JSFunction::kFeedbackCellOffset));
5430 Ld(dst, FieldMemOperand(dst, FeedbackCell::kValueOffset));
5431
5432 // Check if feedback vector is valid.
5433 Ld(scratch, FieldMemOperand(dst, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
5434 Lhu(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
5435 Branch(&done, eq, scratch, Operand(FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE));
5436
5437 // Not valid, load undefined.
5438 LoadRoot(dst, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5439 Branch(fbv_undef);
5440
5441 bind(&done);
5442}
5443
5444void MacroAssembler::LoadNativeContextSlot(Register dst, int index) {
5445 LoadMap(dst, cp);
5446 Ld(dst,
5447 FieldMemOperand(dst, Map::kConstructorOrBackPointerOrNativeContextOffset));
5448 Ld(dst, MemOperand(dst, Context::SlotOffset(index)));
5449}
5450
5451void MacroAssembler::StubPrologue(StackFrame::Type type) {
5452 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5453 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5454 li(scratch, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(type)));
5455 PushCommonFrame(scratch);
5456}
5457
5458void MacroAssembler::Prologue() { PushStandardFrame(a1); }
5459
5460void MacroAssembler::EnterFrame(StackFrame::Type type) {
5461 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5462 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5463 Push(ra, fp);
5464 Move(fp, sp);
5465 if (!StackFrame::IsJavaScript(type)) {
5466 li(kScratchReg, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(type)));
5467 Push(kScratchReg);
5468 }
5469#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5470 if (type == StackFrame::WASM || type == StackFrame::WASM_LIFTOFF_SETUP) {
5471 Push(kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
5472 }
5473#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5474}
5475
5476void MacroAssembler::LeaveFrame(StackFrame::Type type) {
5477 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5478 daddiu(sp, fp, 2 * kPointerSize);
5479 Ld(ra, MemOperand(fp, 1 * kPointerSize));
5480 Ld(fp, MemOperand(fp, 0 * kPointerSize));
5481}
5482
5483void MacroAssembler::EnterExitFrame(Register scratch, int stack_space,
5484 StackFrame::Type frame_type) {
5485 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5486 DCHECK(frame_type == StackFrame::EXIT ||
5487 frame_type == StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT ||
5488 frame_type == StackFrame::API_ACCESSOR_EXIT ||
5489 frame_type == StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT);
5490
5491 using ER = ExternalReference;
5492
5493 // Set up the frame structure on the stack.
5494 static_assert(2 * kPointerSize == ExitFrameConstants::kCallerSPDisplacement);
5495 static_assert(1 * kPointerSize == ExitFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset);
5496 static_assert(0 * kPointerSize == ExitFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset);
5497
5498 // This is how the stack will look:
5499 // fp + 2 (==kCallerSPDisplacement) - old stack's end
5500 // [fp + 1 (==kCallerPCOffset)] - saved old ra
5501 // [fp + 0 (==kCallerFPOffset)] - saved old fp
5502 // [fp - 1 frame_type Smi
5503 // [fp - 2 (==kSPOffset)] - sp of the called function
5504 // fp - (2 + stack_space + alignment) == sp == [fp - kSPOffset] - top of the
5505 // new stack (will contain saved ra)
5506
5507 // Save registers and reserve room for saved entry sp.
5508 daddiu(sp, sp, -2 * kPointerSize - ExitFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp);
5509 Sd(ra, MemOperand(sp, 3 * kPointerSize));
5510 Sd(fp, MemOperand(sp, 2 * kPointerSize));
5511 li(scratch, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(frame_type)));
5512 Sd(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 1 * kPointerSize));
5513
5514 // Set up new frame pointer.
5515 daddiu(fp, sp, ExitFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp);
5516
5517 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5518 Sd(zero_reg, MemOperand(fp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset));
5519 }
5520
5521 // Save the frame pointer and the context in top.
5522 ER c_entry_fp_address =
5523 ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate());
5524 Sd(fp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(c_entry_fp_address, no_reg));
5525
5526 ER context_address = ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate());
5527 Sd(cp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
5528
5529 const int frame_alignment = MacroAssembler::ActivationFrameAlignment();
5530
5531 // Reserve place for the return address, stack space and align the frame
5532 // preparing for calling the runtime function.
5533 DCHECK_GE(stack_space, 0);
5534 Dsubu(sp, sp, Operand((stack_space + 1) * kPointerSize));
5535 if (frame_alignment > 0) {
5536 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
5537 And(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_alignment)); // Align stack.
5538 }
5539
5540 // Set the exit frame sp value to point just before the return address
5541 // location.
5542 daddiu(scratch, sp, kPointerSize);
5543 Sd(scratch, MemOperand(fp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset));
5544}
5545
5546void MacroAssembler::LeaveExitFrame(Register scratch) {
5547 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5548 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5549
5550 using ER = ExternalReference;
5551
5552 // Restore current context from top and clear it in debug mode.
5553 ER context_address = ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate());
5554 Ld(cp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
5555
5556 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5557 li(scratch, Operand(Context::kInvalidContext));
5558 Sd(scratch, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
5559 }
5560
5561 // Clear the top frame.
5562 ER c_entry_fp_address =
5563 ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate());
5564 Sd(zero_reg, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(c_entry_fp_address, no_reg));
5565
5566 // Pop the arguments, restore registers, and return.
5567 mov(sp, fp); // Respect ABI stack constraint.
5568 Ld(fp, MemOperand(sp, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset));
5569 Ld(ra, MemOperand(sp, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset));
5570
5571 daddiu(sp, sp, 2 * kPointerSize);
5572}
5573
5574int MacroAssembler::ActivationFrameAlignment() {
5575#if V8_HOST_ARCH_MIPS || V8_HOST_ARCH_MIPS64
5576 // Running on the real platform. Use the alignment as mandated by the local
5577 // environment.
5578 // Note: This will break if we ever start generating snapshots on one Mips
5579 // platform for another Mips platform with a different alignment.
5580 return base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
5581#else // V8_HOST_ARCH_MIPS
5582 // If we are using the simulator then we should always align to the expected
5583 // alignment. As the simulator is used to generate snapshots we do not know
5584 // if the target platform will need alignment, so this is controlled from a
5585 // flag.
5586 return v8_flags.sim_stack_alignment;
5587#endif // V8_HOST_ARCH_MIPS
5588}
5589
5590void MacroAssembler::SmiUntag(Register dst, const MemOperand& src) {
5591 if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
5592 Lw(dst, MemOperand(src.rm(), SmiWordOffset(src.offset())));
5593 } else {
5594 DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
5595 Lw(dst, src);
5596 SmiUntag(dst);
5597 }
5598}

5600void MacroAssembler::JumpIfSmi(Register value, Label* smi_label,
5601 BranchDelaySlot bd) {
5602 DCHECK_EQ(0, kSmiTag);
5603 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5604 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5605 andi(scratch, value, kSmiTagMask);
5606 Branch(bd, smi_label, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5607}
5608
5609void MacroAssembler::JumpIfNotSmi(Register value, Label* not_smi_label,
5610 BranchDelaySlot bd) {
5611 DCHECK_EQ(0, kSmiTag);
5612 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5613 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5614 andi(scratch, value, kSmiTagMask);
5615 Branch(bd, not_smi_label, ne, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5616}

5618#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DEBUG_CODE
5619
5620void MacroAssembler::Assert(Condition cc, AbortReason reason, Register rs,
5621 Operand rt) {
5622 if (v8_flags.debug_code) Check(cc, reason, rs, rt);
5623}
5624
5625void MacroAssembler::AssertJSAny(Register object, Register map_tmp,
5626 Register tmp, AbortReason abort_reason) {
5627 if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
5628
5629 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5630 DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, map_tmp, tmp));
5631 Label ok;
5632
5633 JumpIfSmi(object, &ok);
5634
5635 GetObjectType(object, map_tmp, tmp);
5636
5637 Branch(&ok, kUnsignedLessThanEqual, tmp, Operand(LAST_NAME_TYPE));
5638
5639 Branch(&ok, kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual, tmp, Operand(FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE));
5640
5641 Branch(&ok, kEqual, map_tmp, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap);
5642
5643 Branch(&ok, kEqual, map_tmp, RootIndex::kBigIntMap);
5644
5645 Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5646
5647 Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
5648
5649 Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kFalseValue);
5650
5651 Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kNullValue);
5652
5653 Abort(abort_reason);
5654 bind(&ok);
5655}
5656
5657void MacroAssembler::AssertNotSmi(Register object) {
5658 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5659 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5660 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
5661 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5662 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5663 andi(scratch, object, kSmiTagMask);
5664 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmi, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5665 }
5666}
5667
5668void MacroAssembler::AssertSmi(Register object) {
5669 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5670 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5671 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
5672 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5673 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5674 andi(scratch, object, kSmiTagMask);
5675 Check(eq, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmi, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5676 }
5677}
5678
5679void MacroAssembler::AssertStackIsAligned() {
5680 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5681 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5682 const int frame_alignment = ActivationFrameAlignment();
5683 const int frame_alignment_mask = frame_alignment - 1;
5684
5685 if (frame_alignment > kPointerSize) {
5686 Label alignment_as_expected;
5687 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
5688 {
5689 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5690 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5691 andi(scratch, sp, frame_alignment_mask);
5692 Branch(&alignment_as_expected, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5693 }
5694 // Don't use Check here, as it will call Runtime_Abort re-entering here.
5695 stop();
5696 bind(&alignment_as_expected);
5697 }
5698 }
5699}
5700
5701void MacroAssembler::AssertConstructor(Register object) {
5702 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5703 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5704 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5705 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
5706 SmiTst(object, t8);
5707 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotAConstructor, t8,
5708 Operand(zero_reg));
5709
5710 LoadMap(t8, object);
5711 Lbu(t8, FieldMemOperand(t8, Map::kBitFieldOffset));
5712 And(t8, t8, Operand(Map::Bits1::IsConstructorBit::kMask));
5713 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAConstructor, t8, Operand(zero_reg));
5714 }
5715}
5716
5717void MacroAssembler::AssertFunction(Register object) {
5718 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5719 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5720 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5721 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
5722 SmiTst(object, t8);
5723 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotAFunction, t8,
5724 Operand(zero_reg));
5725 push(object);
5726 LoadMap(object, object);
5727 GetInstanceTypeRange(object, object, FIRST_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE, t8);
5728 Check(ls, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAFunction, t8,
5729 Operand(LAST_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE - FIRST_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE));
5730 pop(object);
5731 }
5732}
5733
5734void MacroAssembler::AssertCallableFunction(Register object) {
5735 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5736 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5737 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5738 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
5739 SmiTst(object, t8);
5740 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotAFunction, t8,
5741 Operand(zero_reg));
5742 push(object);
5743 LoadMap(object, object);
5744 GetInstanceTypeRange(object, object, FIRST_CALLABLE_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE, t8);
5745 Check(ls, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotACallableFunction, t8,
5746 Operand(LAST_CALLABLE_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE -
5747 FIRST_CALLABLE_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE));
5748 pop(object);
5749 }
5750}
5751
5752void MacroAssembler::AssertBoundFunction(Register object) {
5753 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5754 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5755 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5756 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
5757 SmiTst(object, t8);
5758 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotABoundFunction, t8,
5759 Operand(zero_reg));
5760 GetObjectType(object, t8, t8);
5761 Check(eq, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotABoundFunction, t8,
5762 Operand(JS_BOUND_FUNCTION_TYPE));
5763 }
5764}
5765
5766void MacroAssembler::AssertGeneratorObject(Register object) {
5767 if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
5768 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5769 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5770 static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
5771 SmiTst(object, t8);
5772 Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotAGeneratorObject, t8,
5773 Operand(zero_reg));
5774 GetObjectType(object, t8, t8);
5775 Dsubu(t8, t8, Operand(FIRST_JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE));
5776 Check(
5777 ls, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAGeneratorObject, t8,
5778 Operand(LAST_JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE - FIRST_JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE));
5779}
5780
5781void MacroAssembler::AssertUndefinedOrAllocationSite(Register object,
5782 Register scratch) {
5783 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5784 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5785 Label done_checking;
5786 AssertNotSmi(object);
5787 LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5788 Branch(&done_checking, eq, object, Operand(scratch));
5789 GetObjectType(object, scratch, scratch);
5790 Assert(eq, AbortReason::kExpectedUndefinedOrCell, scratch,
5791 Operand(ALLOCATION_SITE_TYPE));
5792 bind(&done_checking);
5793 }
5794}

5796#endif // V8_ENABLE_DEBUG_CODE
5797
5798void MacroAssembler::Float32Max(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
5799 FPURegister src2, Label* out_of_line) {
5800 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5801 if (src1 == src2) {
5802 Move_s(dst, src1);
5803 return;
5804 }
5805
5806 // Check if one of operands is NaN.
5807 CompareIsNanF32(src1, src2);
5808 BranchTrueF(out_of_line);
5809
5810 if (kArchVariant >= kMips64r6) {
5811 max_s(dst, src1, src2);
5812 } else {
5813 Label return_left, return_right, done;
5814
5815 CompareF32(OLT, src1, src2);
5816 BranchTrueShortF(&return_right);
5817 CompareF32(OLT, src2, src1);
5818 BranchTrueShortF(&return_left);
5819
5820 // Operands are equal, but check for +/-0.
5821 {
5822 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5823 mfc1(t8, src1);
5824 dsll32(t8, t8, 0);
5825 Branch(&return_left, eq, t8, Operand(zero_reg));
5826 Branch(&return_right);
5827 }
5828
5829 bind(&return_right);
5830 if (src2 != dst) {
5831 Move_s(dst, src2);
5832 }
5833 Branch(&done);
5834
5835 bind(&return_left);
5836 if (src1 != dst) {
5837 Move_s(dst, src1);
5838 }
5839
5840 bind(&done);
5841 }
5842}
5843
5844void MacroAssembler::Float32MaxOutOfLine(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
5845 FPURegister src2) {
5846 add_s(dst, src1, src2);
5847}
5848
5849void MacroAssembler::Float32Min(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
5850 FPURegister src2, Label* out_of_line) {
5851 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5852 if (src1 == src2) {
5853 Move_s(dst, src1);
5854 return;
5855 }
5856
5857 // Check if one of operands is NaN.
5858 CompareIsNanF32(src1, src2);
5859 BranchTrueF(out_of_line);
5860
5861 if (kArchVariant >= kMips64r6) {
5862 min_s(dst, src1, src2);
5863 } else {
5864 Label return_left, return_right, done;
5865
5866 CompareF32(OLT, src1, src2);
5867 BranchTrueShortF(&return_left);
5868 CompareF32(OLT, src2, src1);
5869 BranchTrueShortF(&return_right);
5870
5871 // Left equals right => check for -0.
5872 {
5873 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5874 mfc1(t8, src1);
5875 dsll32(t8, t8, 0);
5876 Branch(&return_right, eq, t8, Operand(zero_reg));
5877 Branch(&return_left);
5878 }
5879
5880 bind(&return_right);
5881 if (src2 != dst) {
5882 Move_s(dst, src2);
5883 }
5884 Branch(&done);
5885
5886 bind(&return_left);
5887 if (src1 != dst) {
5888 Move_s(dst, src1);
5889 }
5890
5891 bind(&done);
5892 }
5893}

5999
6000int MacroAssembler::CalculateStackPassedWords(int num_reg_arguments,
6001 int num_double_arguments) {
6002 int stack_passed_words = 0;
6003 int num_args = num_reg_arguments + num_double_arguments;
6004
6005 // Up to eight arguments are passed in FPURegisters and GPRegisters.
6006 if (num_args > kRegisterPassedArguments) {
6007 stack_passed_words = num_args - kRegisterPassedArguments;
6008 }
6009 stack_passed_words += kCArgSlotCount;
6010 return stack_passed_words;
6011}
6012
6013void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_reg_arguments,
6014 int num_double_arguments,
6015 Register scratch) {
6016 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6017 int frame_alignment = ActivationFrameAlignment();
6018
6019 // n64: Up to eight simple arguments in a0..a3, a4..a7, No argument slots.
6020 // O32: Up to four simple arguments are passed in registers a0..a3.
6021 // Those four arguments must have reserved argument slots on the stack for
6022 // mips, even though those argument slots are not normally used.
6023 // Both ABIs: Remaining arguments are pushed on the stack, above (higher
6024 // address than) the (O32) argument slots. (arg slot calculation handled by
6025 // CalculateStackPassedWords()).
6026 int stack_passed_arguments =
6027 CalculateStackPassedWords(num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments);
6028 if (frame_alignment > kPointerSize) {
6029 // Make stack end at alignment and make room for num_arguments - 4 words
6030 // and the original value of sp.
6031 mov(scratch, sp);
6032 Dsubu(sp, sp, Operand((stack_passed_arguments + 1) * kPointerSize));
6033 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
6034 And(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_alignment));
6035 Sd(scratch, MemOperand(sp, stack_passed_arguments * kPointerSize));
6036 } else {
6037 Dsubu(sp, sp, Operand(stack_passed_arguments * kPointerSize));
6038 }
6039}
6040
6041void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_reg_arguments,
6042 Register scratch) {
6043 PrepareCallCFunction(num_reg_arguments, 0, scratch);
6044}
6045
6046int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(ExternalReference function,
6047 int num_reg_arguments,
6048 int num_double_arguments,
6049 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
6050 Label* return_location) {
6051 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6052 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6053 li(t9, function);
6054 return CallCFunctionHelper(t9, num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments,
6055 set_isolate_data_slots, return_location);
6056}
6057
6058int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(Register function, int num_reg_arguments,
6059 int num_double_arguments,
6060 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
6061 Label* return_location) {
6062 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6063 return CallCFunctionHelper(function, num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments,
6064 set_isolate_data_slots, return_location);
6065}
6066
6067int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(ExternalReference function, int num_arguments,
6068 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
6069 Label* return_location) {
6070 return CallCFunction(function, num_arguments, 0, set_isolate_data_slots,
6071 return_location);
6072}
6073
6074int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(Register function, int num_arguments,
6075 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
6076 Label* return_location) {
6077 return CallCFunction(function, num_arguments, 0, set_isolate_data_slots,
6078 return_location);
6079}
6080
6081int MacroAssembler::CallCFunctionHelper(
6082 Register function, int num_reg_arguments, int num_double_arguments,
6083 SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots, Label* return_location) {
6084 DCHECK_LE(num_reg_arguments + num_double_arguments, kMaxCParameters);
6085 DCHECK(has_frame());
6086
6087 Label get_pc;
6088
6089 // Make sure that the stack is aligned before calling a C function unless
6090 // running in the simulator. The simulator has its own alignment check which
6091 // provides more information.
6092 // The argument stots are presumed to have been set up by
6093 // PrepareCallCFunction. The C function must be called via t9, for mips ABI.
6094
6095#if V8_HOST_ARCH_MIPS || V8_HOST_ARCH_MIPS64
6096 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6097 int frame_alignment = base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
6098 int frame_alignment_mask = frame_alignment - 1;
6099 if (frame_alignment > kPointerSize) {
6100 DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
6101 Label alignment_as_expected;
6102 {
6103 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6104 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6105 And(scratch, sp, Operand(frame_alignment_mask));
6106 Branch(&alignment_as_expected, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6107 }
6108 // Don't use Check here, as it will call Runtime_Abort possibly
6109 // re-entering here.
6110 stop();
6111 bind(&alignment_as_expected);
6112 }
6113 }
6114#endif // V8_HOST_ARCH_MIPS
6115
6116 // Just call directly. The function called cannot cause a GC, or
6117 // allow preemption, so the return address in the link register
6118 // stays correct.
6119 {
6120 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6121 if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
6122 if (function != t9) {
6123 mov(t9, function);
6124 function = t9;
6125 }
6126
6127 // Save the frame pointer and PC so that the stack layout remains
6128 // iterable, even without an ExitFrame which normally exists between JS
6129 // and C frames. 't' registers are caller-saved so this is safe as a
6130 // scratch register.
6131 Register pc_scratch = t1;
6132 DCHECK(!AreAliased(pc_scratch, function));
6133 CHECK(root_array_available());
6134
6135 LoadAddressPCRelative(pc_scratch, &get_pc);
6136
6137 Sd(pc_scratch,
6138 ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerPC));
6139 Sd(fp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP));
6140 }
6141
6142 Call(function);
6143 int call_pc_offset = pc_offset();
6144 bind(&get_pc);
6145
6146 if (return_location) bind(return_location);
6147
6148 if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
6149 // We don't unset the PC; the FP is the source of truth.
6150 Sd(zero_reg,
6151 ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP));
6152 }
6153
6154 int stack_passed_arguments =
6155 CalculateStackPassedWords(num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments);
6156
6157 if (base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment() > kPointerSize) {
6158 Ld(sp, MemOperand(sp, stack_passed_arguments * kPointerSize));
6159 } else {
6160 Daddu(sp, sp, Operand(stack_passed_arguments * kPointerSize));
6161 }
6162
6163 set_pc_for_safepoint();
6164
6165 return call_pc_offset;
6166 }
6167}
6168
6169#undef BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK
6170
6171void MacroAssembler::CheckPageFlag(Register object, Register scratch, int mask,
6172 Condition cc, Label* condition_met) {
6173 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6174 And(scratch, object, Operand(~MemoryChunk::GetAlignmentMaskForAssembler()));
6175 Ld(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, MemoryChunk::FlagsOffset()));
6176 And(scratch, scratch, Operand(mask));
6177 Branch(condition_met, cc, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6178}
6179
6180Register GetRegisterThatIsNotOneOf(Register reg1, Register reg2, Register reg3,
6181 Register reg4, Register reg5,
6182 Register reg6) {
6183 RegList regs = {reg1, reg2, reg3, reg4, reg5, reg6};
6184
6185 const RegisterConfiguration* config = RegisterConfiguration::Default();
6186 for (int i = 0; i < config->num_allocatable_general_registers(); ++i) {
6187 int code = config->GetAllocatableGeneralCode(i);
6188 Register candidate = Register::from_code(code);
6189 if (regs.has(candidate)) continue;
6190 return candidate;
6191 }
6192 UNREACHABLE();
6193}
6194
6195void MacroAssembler::ComputeCodeStartAddress(Register dst) {
6196 // This push on ra and the pop below together ensure that we restore the
6197 // register ra, which is needed while computing the code start address.
6198 push(ra);
6199
6200 // The nal instruction puts the address of the current instruction into
6201 // the return address (ra) register, which we can use later on.
6202 if (kArchVariant == kMips64r6) {
6203 addiupc(ra, 1);
6204 } else {
6205 nal();
6206 nop();
6207 }
6208 int pc = pc_offset();
6209 li(dst, Operand(pc));
6210 Dsubu(dst, ra, dst);
6211
6212 pop(ra); // Restore ra
6213}
6214
6215void MacroAssembler::CallForDeoptimization(Builtin target, int, Label* exit,
6216 DeoptimizeKind kind, Label* ret,
6217 Label*) {
6218 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6219 BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6220 Ld(t9,
6221 MemOperand(kRootRegister, IsolateData::BuiltinEntrySlotOffset(target)));
6222 Call(t9);
6223 DCHECK_EQ(SizeOfCodeGeneratedSince(exit),
6224 (kind == DeoptimizeKind::kLazy) ? Deoptimizer::kLazyDeoptExitSize
6225 : Deoptimizer::kEagerDeoptExitSize);
6226}

6228void MacroAssembler::LoadCodeInstructionStart(

6230 CodeEntrypointTag tag) {
6231 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6232 Ld(destination, FieldMemOperand(code_data_container_object,
6233 Code::kInstructionStartOffset));
6234}
6235
6236void MacroAssembler::CallCodeObject(Register code_data_container_object,
6237 CodeEntrypointTag tag) {

6239 LoadCodeInstructionStart(code_data_container_object,
6240 code_data_container_object, tag);

6242}

6244void MacroAssembler::JumpCodeObject(Register code_data_container_object,
6245 CodeEntrypointTag tag, JumpMode jump_mode) {

6248 LoadCodeInstructionStart(code_data_container_object,
6249 code_data_container_object, tag);
6250 Jump(code_data_container_object);

6253void MacroAssembler::CallJSFunction(Register function_object) {
6254 Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
6255#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6256 LoadCodeEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(
6257 code,
6258 FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
6259 Call(code);
6260#else
6261 Ld(code, FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
6262 CallCodeObject(code, kJSEntrypointTag);
6263#endif
6264}
6265
6266void MacroAssembler::JumpJSFunction(Register function_object,
6267 JumpMode jump_mode) {
6268 Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
6269#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6270 LoadCodeEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(
6271 code,
6272 FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
6273 DCHECK_EQ(jump_mode, JumpMode::kJump);
6274 Jump(code);
6275#else
6276 Ld(code, FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
6277 JumpCodeObject(code, kJSEntrypointTag, jump_mode);
6278#endif
6279}

6281#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6282
6283void MacroAssembler::ResolveWasmCodePointer(Register target) {
6284 ExternalReference global_jump_table =
6285 ExternalReference::wasm_code_pointer_table();
6286 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6287 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6288 xor_(zero_reg, scratch, scratch);
6289 li(scratch, global_jump_table);
6290 static_assert(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry) == kSystemPointerSize);
6291 sll(target, target, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
6292 daddu(scratch, scratch, target);
6293 Ld(target, MemOperand(scratch, 0));
6294}
6295
6296void MacroAssembler::CallWasmCodePointer(Register target,
6297 CallJumpMode call_jump_mode) {
6298 ResolveWasmCodePointer(target);
6299 if (call_jump_mode == CallJumpMode::kTailCall) {
6300 Jump(target);
6301 } else {
6302 Call(target);
6303 }
6304}
6305
6306#endif
6307
6308namespace {
6309
6310#ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6311// Only used when leaptiering is disabled.
6312void TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(MacroAssembler* masm,
6313 Register optimized_code_entry, Register scratch1,
6314 Register scratch2) {
6315 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
6316 // -- a0 : actual argument count
6317 // -- a3 : new target (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
6318 // -- a1 : target function (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
6319 // -----------------------------------
6320 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
6321 DCHECK(!AreAliased(optimized_code_entry, a1, a3, scratch1, scratch2));
6322
6323 Label heal_optimized_code_slot;
6324
6325 // If the optimized code is cleared, go to runtime to update the optimization
6326 // marker field.
6327 __ LoadWeakValue(optimized_code_entry, optimized_code_entry,
6328 &heal_optimized_code_slot);
6329
6330 // The entry references a CodeWrapper object. Unwrap it now.
6331 __ Ld(optimized_code_entry,
6332 FieldMemOperand(optimized_code_entry, CodeWrapper::kCodeOffset));
6333
6334 // Check if the optimized code is marked for deopt. If it is, call the
6335 // runtime to clear it.
6336 __ TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimizationAndJump(optimized_code_entry, scratch1,
6337 ne, &heal_optimized_code_slot);
6338
6339 // Optimized code is good, get it into the closure and link the closure into
6340 // the optimized functions list, then tail call the optimized code.
6341 // The feedback vector is no longer used, so re-use it as a scratch
6342 // register.
6343 __ ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(optimized_code_entry, a1, scratch1,
6344 scratch2);
6345
6346 static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == a2, "ABI mismatch");
6347 __ LoadCodeInstructionStart(a2, optimized_code_entry, kJSEntrypointTag);
6348 __ Jump(a2);
6349
6350 // Optimized code slot contains deoptimized code or code is cleared and
6351 // optimized code marker isn't updated. Evict the code, update the marker
6352 // and re-enter the closure's code.
6353 __ bind(&heal_optimized_code_slot);
6354 __ GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kHealOptimizedCodeSlot);
6355}
6356#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6357
6358} // namespace
6359
6360#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DEBUG_CODE
6361void MacroAssembler::AssertFeedbackCell(Register object, Register scratch) {
6362 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6363 GetObjectType(object, scratch, scratch);
6364 Assert(eq, AbortReason::kExpectedFeedbackCell, scratch,
6365 Operand(FEEDBACK_CELL_TYPE));
6366 }
6367}
6368void MacroAssembler::AssertFeedbackVector(Register object, Register scratch) {
6369 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6370 GetObjectType(object, scratch, scratch);
6371 Assert(eq, AbortReason::kExpectedFeedbackVector, scratch,
6372 Operand(FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE));
6373 }
6374}
6375#endif // V8_ENABLE_DEBUG_CODE
6376
6377void MacroAssembler::ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(
6378 Register optimized_code, Register closure, Register scratch1,
6379 Register scratch2) {
6380 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6381 DCHECK(!AreAliased(optimized_code, closure, scratch1, scratch2));
6382
6383#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6384 UNREACHABLE();
6385#else
6386 // Store code entry in the closure.
6387 Sd(optimized_code, FieldMemOperand(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
6388 mov(scratch1, optimized_code); // Write barrier clobbers scratch1 below.
6389 RecordWriteField(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset, scratch1, scratch2,
6390 kRAHasNotBeenSaved, SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore,
6391 SmiCheck::kOmit);
6392#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6393}
6394
6395void MacroAssembler::GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(
6396 Runtime::FunctionId function_id) {
6397 // ----------- S t a t e -------------
6398 // -- a0 : actual argument count
6399 // -- a1 : target function (preserved for callee)
6400 // -- a3 : new target (preserved for callee)
6401 // -----------------------------------
6402 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6403 {
6404 FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
6405 // Push a copy of the target function, the new target and the actual
6406 // argument count.
6407 // Push function as parameter to the runtime call.
6408 SmiTag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
6409 Push(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister,
6410 kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister, kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister);
6411
6412 CallRuntime(function_id, 1);
6413 // Restore target function, new target and actual argument count.
6414 Pop(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister,
6415 kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
6416 SmiUntag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
6417 }
6418
6419 static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == a2, "ABI mismatch");
6420 LoadCodeInstructionStart(a2, v0, kJSEntrypointTag);
6421 Jump(a2);
6422}
6423
6424void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVectorFlagsAndJumpIfNeedsProcessing(
6425 Register flags, Register feedback_vector, CodeKind current_code_kind,
6426 Label* flags_need_processing) {
6427 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6428 DCHECK(CodeKindCanTierUp(current_code_kind));
6429 Register scratch = t2;
6430 uint32_t flag_mask =
6431 FeedbackVector::FlagMaskForNeedsProcessingCheckFrom(current_code_kind);
6432 Lhu(flags, FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::kFlagsOffset));
6433 And(scratch, flags, Operand(flag_mask));
6434 Branch(flags_need_processing, ne, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6435}
6436
6437void MacroAssembler::OptimizeCodeOrTailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(
6438 Register flags, Register feedback_vector) {
6439 ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6440#ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6441 // In the leaptiering case, we don't load optimized code from the feedback
6442 // vector so only need to call CompileOptimized or FunctionLogNextExecution
6443 // here. See also LoadFeedbackVectorFlagsAndJumpIfNeedsProcessing above.
6444 Label needs_logging;
6445 {
6446 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6447 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6448 And(scratch, flags,
6449 Operand(FeedbackVector::kFlagsTieringStateIsAnyRequested));
6450 Branch(&needs_logging, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6451 }
6452
6453 GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kCompileOptimized);
6454
6455 bind(&needs_logging);
6456 GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kFunctionLogNextExecution);
6457#else
6458 Label maybe_has_optimized_code, maybe_needs_logging;
6459 // Check if optimized code marker is available.
6460 {
6461 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6462 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6463 And(scratch, flags,
6464 Operand(FeedbackVector::kFlagsTieringStateIsAnyRequested));
6465 Branch(&maybe_needs_logging, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6466 }
6467
6468 GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kCompileOptimized);
6469
6470 bind(&maybe_needs_logging);
6471 {
6472 UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6473 Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6474 And(scratch, flags, Operand(FeedbackVector::LogNextExecutionBit::kMask));
6475 Branch(&maybe_has_optimized_code, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6476 }
6477
6478 GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kFunctionLogNextExecution);
6479
6480 bind(&maybe_has_optimized_code);
6481 Register optimized_code_entry = flags;
6482 Ld(optimized_code_entry,
6483 FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector,
6484 FeedbackVector::kMaybeOptimizedCodeOffset));
6485 TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(this, optimized_code_entry, t3, a5);
6486#endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
6487}
6488
6489// Calls an API function. Allocates HandleScope, extracts returned value
6490// from handle and propagates exceptions. Clobbers C argument registers
6491// and C caller-saved registers. Restores context. On return removes
6492// (*argc_operand + slots_to_drop_on_return) * kSystemPointerSize
6493// (GCed, includes the call JS arguments space and the additional space
6494// allocated for the fast call).
6495void CallApiFunctionAndReturn(MacroAssembler* masm, bool with_profiling,
6496 Register function_address,
6497 ExternalReference thunk_ref, Register thunk_arg,
6498 int slots_to_drop_on_return,
6499 MemOperand* argc_operand,
6500 MemOperand return_value_operand) {
6501 using ER = ExternalReference;
6502
6503 Isolate* isolate = masm->isolate();
6504 MemOperand next_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6505 ER::handle_scope_next_address(isolate), no_reg);
6506 MemOperand limit_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6507 ER::handle_scope_limit_address(isolate), no_reg);
6508 MemOperand level_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6509 ER::handle_scope_level_address(isolate), no_reg);
6510
6511 Register return_value = v0;
6512 Register scratch = a4;
6513 Register scratch2 = a5;
6514
6515 // Allocate HandleScope in callee-saved registers.
6516 // We will need to restore the HandleScope after the call to the API function,
6517 // by allocating it in callee-saved registers it'll be preserved by C code.
6518 Register prev_next_address_reg = s0;
6519 Register prev_limit_reg = s1;
6520 Register prev_level_reg = s2;
6521
6522 // C arguments (kCArgRegs[0/1]) are expected to be initialized outside, so
6523 // this function must not corrupt them (return_value overlaps with
6524 // kCArgRegs[0] but that's ok because we start using it only after the C
6525 // call).
6526 DCHECK(!AreAliased(kCArgRegs[0], kCArgRegs[1], // C args
6527 scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
6528 // function_address and thunk_arg might overlap but this function must not
6529 // corrupted them until the call is made (i.e. overlap with return_value is
6530 // fine).
6531 DCHECK(!AreAliased(function_address, // incoming parameters
6532 scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
6533 DCHECK(!AreAliased(thunk_arg, // incoming parameters
6534 scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
6535
6536 {
6537 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
6538 "Allocate HandleScope in callee-save registers.");
6539 __ Ld(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
6540 __ Ld(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
6541 __ Lw(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
6542 __ Addu(scratch, prev_level_reg, Operand(1));
6543 __ Sw(scratch, level_mem_op);
6544 }
6545
6546 Label profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, done_api_call;
6547 if (with_profiling) {
6548 __ RecordComment("Check if profiler or side effects check is enabled");
6549 __ Lb(scratch,
6550 __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kExecutionMode));
6551 __ Branch(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, ne, scratch,
6552 Operand(zero_reg));
6553#ifdef V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
6554 __ RecordComment("Check if RCS is enabled");
6555 __ li(scratch, ER::address_of_runtime_stats_flag());
6556 __ Lw(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, 0));
6557 __ Branch(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, ne, scratch,
6558 Operand(zero_reg));
6559#endif // V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
6560 }
6561
6562 __ RecordComment("Call the api function directly.");
6563 __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(function_address);
6564 __ bind(&done_api_call);
6565
6566 Label propagate_exception;
6567 Label delete_allocated_handles;
6568 Label leave_exit_frame;
6569
6570 __ RecordComment("Load value from ReturnValue.");
6571 __ Ld(return_value, return_value_operand);
6572
6573 {
6574 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
6575 masm,
6576 "No more valid handles (the result handle was the last one)."
6577 "Restore previous handle scope.");
6578 __ Sd(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
6579 if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6580 __ Lw(scratch, level_mem_op);
6581 __ Subu(scratch, scratch, Operand(1));
6582 __ Check(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedLevelAfterReturnFromApiCall, scratch,
6583 Operand(prev_level_reg));
6584 }
6585 __ Sw(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
6586 __ Ld(scratch, limit_mem_op);
6587 __ Branch(&delete_allocated_handles, ne, prev_limit_reg, Operand(scratch));
6588 }
6589
6590 __ RecordComment("Leave the API exit frame.");
6591 __ bind(&leave_exit_frame);
6592
6593 Register argc_reg = prev_limit_reg;
6594 if (argc_operand != nullptr) {
6595 // Load the number of stack slots to drop before LeaveExitFrame modifies sp.
6596 __ Ld(argc_reg, *argc_operand);
6597 }
6598
6599 __ LeaveExitFrame(scratch);
6600
6601 {
6602 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
6603 "Check if the function scheduled an exception.");
6604 __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
6605 __ Ld(scratch2, __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6606 ER::exception_address(isolate), no_reg));
6607 __ Branch(&propagate_exception, ne, scratch, Operand(scratch2));
6608 }
6609
6610 __ AssertJSAny(return_value, scratch, scratch2,
6611 AbortReason::kAPICallReturnedInvalidObject);
6612
6613 if (argc_operand == nullptr) {
6614 DCHECK_NE(slots_to_drop_on_return, 0);
6615 __ Daddu(sp, sp, Operand(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
6616 } else {
6617 // {argc_operand} was loaded into {argc_reg} above.
6618 if (slots_to_drop_on_return != 0) {
6619 __ Daddu(sp, sp, Operand(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
6620 }
6621 __ Dlsa(sp, sp, argc_reg, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
6622 }
6623
6624 __ Ret();
6625
6626 if (with_profiling) {
6627 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Call the api function via thunk wrapper.");
6628 __ bind(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
6629 // Additional parameter is the address of the actual callback.
6630 if (thunk_arg.is_valid()) {
6631 MemOperand thunk_arg_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6632 IsolateFieldId::kApiCallbackThunkArgument);
6633 __ Sd(thunk_arg, thunk_arg_mem_op);
6634 }
6635 __ li(scratch, thunk_ref);
6636 __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(scratch);
6637 __ Branch(&done_api_call);
6638 }
6639
6640 __ RecordComment("An exception was thrown. Propagate it.");
6641 __ bind(&propagate_exception);
6642 __ TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kPropagateException);
6643
6644 {
6645 ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
6646 masm, "HandleScope limit has changed. Delete allocated extensions.");
6647 __ bind(&delete_allocated_handles);
6648 __ Sd(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
6649 // Save the return value in a callee-save register.
6650 Register saved_result = prev_limit_reg;
6651 __ mov(saved_result, v0);
6652 __ mov(kCArgRegs[0], v0);
6653 __ PrepareCallCFunction(1, prev_level_reg);
6654 __ li(kCArgRegs[0], ER::isolate_address());
6655 __ CallCFunction(ER::delete_handle_scope_extensions(), 1);
6656 __ mov(v0, saved_result);
6657 __ jmp(&leave_exit_frame);
6658 }
6659}
6660
6661} // namespace internal
6662} // namespace v8

6664#undef __
6665
6666#endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_MIPS64
